Explain the difference between using a computer program and programming a computer.

A computer executes very simple instructions in rapid succession.
A computer program is a sequence of instructions and decisions; made in order for a computer to execute them.
Using a computer program is the act of using the result of the execution of a computer program, i.e. a sequence of instructions and decisions.
However, it is not the act of writing the sequence of instructions and decisions that the computer should execute.
Programming a computer is the act of writing the sequence of instructions and decisions that are a computer program.
